9 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Employees Insurance
Plan; defining terms; requiring certain provisions to
10 be included in certain contract; prohibiting pharmacy
benefits manager (PBM) from changing drug placement
11 on a formulary without certain written authorization;
prohibiting PBM from prohibiting certain guarantees
12 of set pricing; prohibiting PBM from including
certain plan designs without certain impact analysis
13 and certain written approval of certain provisions by
state plan; prohibiting PBM from establishing certain
14 less favorable network terms; prohibiting
establishment of certain gag clauses by certain PBM;
15 prohibiting establishment of certain contract
provisions that create certain conditions that
16 exclude certain pharmacies without certain
justification; requiring PBM to disclose certain
17 affiliates or subcontractors prior to awarding of
certain contract; requiring certain rebates to be
18 passed through to state plan; construing provisions;
establishing certain determination of certain
19 guarantees; requiring PBM to maintain certain System
and Organization Controls (SOC) Type 2 certification;
20 requiring PBM to provide certain written impact
analysis prior to approval of changes to certain
21 contract provisions; requiring certain impact
analysis to include certain provisions; requiring PBM
22 to submit certain report including certain claim-
level reporting data; requiring certain report to
23 include certain provisions; allowing certain contract
proposal to be scored based on certain provisions;
24
